=== FILE 1: tasks.csv ===
One row per Excel data row. Columns in this exact order:

source_sheet,source_row,work_type,title,business_reason,platform_area,reviewer_name,primary_assignee,secondary_assignee,tertiary_assignee,overflow_assignees,start_date,closed_date,status,effort_days,completion_pct,jira_reference,import_notes

Rules:
- work_type: "Enhancement" for Enhancements sheet, "Automation" for Automation sheet.
- Task Description parse:
    * First non-label line before any "Why:/Reason:/Where:/Platform:/System:" label → title.
    * Content after "Why:" or "Reason:" → business_reason (strip the label).
    * Content after "Where:" or "Platform:" or "System:" → platform_area.
    * Other labels (How:, Impact:, What:, When:) → append to business_reason as "<Label>: <text>".
    * If no labels found, whole cell → title; business_reason and platform_area blank.
    * Collapse internal newlines inside each field to single spaces.
- Assignees: split Assignee cell on "/". Trim each. Apply canonical map above.
    * Position 1 → primary_assignee (required; if blank, leave blank and flag).
    * Position 2 → secondary_assignee.
    * Position 3 → tertiary_assignee.
    * Position 4+ → overflow_assignees (comma-separated canonical names) AND add "4+ assignees in source" to import_notes.
- reviewer_name: take FIRST name in Reviewer cell after canonical mapping. If multiple present, append "extra reviewers: <rest>" to import_notes.
- Dates (start_date, closed_date): output DD/MMM/YYYY (e.g. 05/Jul/2025).
    * Parse DD/MM/YYYY, DD/MMM/YYYY, DD-MMM-YY, and Excel serial numbers.
    * If format is ambiguous (could be US MM/DD or EU DD/MM, e.g. "7/3/2025"): leave blank and add "<column> ambiguous: <raw value>" to import_notes.
    * Text values (TBD, NA, Pending, blank): leave blank.
    * For Status=Closed rows with blank closed_date: leave blank and add "closed but no closed_date" to import_notes. Do NOT guess.
- status: exact match to Queued / In Progress / On Hold / Closed / Cancelled.
    * "Pending(...)" or any variant → "On Hold" + add "status was: <raw>" to import_notes.
    * Anything else → "Queued" + flag.
- effort_days: numeric; blank or non-numeric → 0 + flag.
- completion_pct: numeric 0–100. NA → 0. Values ≤ 1 with no "%" treated as literal percent (NOT multiplied by 100).
- jira_reference: value from the JIRA column if present. If blank, scan Task Description AND every line of Status Update for first match of [A-Z]{2,6}-\d+ OR atlassian.net URL. Use that. If multiple, take first.
- import_notes: pipe-separated list of all flags for this row. Blank if none.

